Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with semantic parsing, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP). 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper discusses machine learning models for semantic parsing. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper focuses on developing a novel graph-based decoding framework for semantic parsing. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a possible category as the paper deals with translating natural language text to code signatures, which is relevant to software engineering. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also a possible category as the paper deals with parsing natural language text to programming language code signatures.
